		{"id":"6a48ae2f9722088f","type":"text","text":"classic arcade roguelike aesthetic\nreal time\narcade action / adventure\n\nWander your way through dreamland in search of a solution to a cosmic mystery.\n\nemergent behavior meets quick arcade fun\n\nNon player characters are led by a goal oriented action planning system. Most NPCs are designed to behave organically. Some NPCs are simple minded, wandering around, eating, hunting, etc. Others are more clever and will follow more long term goals.\n\nComponents are objects that can be attached to another object to give them extra attributes and functions. For example, an inventory component, a health component, a hunger component, etc.\n\nItems are objects that can be picked up and used to create effects or activate powers or game states. They optionally have a cooldown, a cast time, and multiple charges.\n\nPowerups are objects that entities can run into and are picked up automatically. Most powerups are simple stat-ups.\n\nThe game world will be tile-based, split into squares of 16x16. Every cell will have properties determining its type, traversability, skin, etc. There should be a competent API to generate terrain. There will be static terrain and destructible terrain. Static terrain should appear to tile together when adjacent. Tiles can be created or destroyed dynamically with little overhead.\n\n----\n\nenvironmental interactions will affect game logic for sure. additionally, i imagine one creature that can pick up and rearrange terrain, i also imagine another creature that can create slime blocks that are destroyed in one hit. i also imagine another creature that can destroy a lot of terrain at once. basically, creating, modifying, and destroying terrain properties should be as easy and performant as possible. data-oriented design and composition is something that is very important to me. additionally, i imagine eventually implementing a feature where entities are simulated (not rendered) like a lower level and optimized simulation of their actions that way their state still changes even when they are offscreen or sufficiently far away.","x":-12920,"y":-22953,"width":440,"height":1096},
		{"id":"2cce492772a12f33","type":"text","text":"- [ ] make tiles actually take damage when they're attacked\n- [ ] fog of war\n- [ ] timer lowered to 1:00\n- [ ] some sort of system to spawn fruits on the map\n- [ ] another system to spawn creatures on the map\n- [ ] post-game menu to actually count how many fruits you collected\n- [ ] build a complete map\n- [ ] claw attack","x":-12462,"y":-22526,"width":440,"height":456},
		{"id":"b66ba903dbc4db76","type":"text","text":"The player is a Caroweasel, a little animal right in the middle of the local food chain.\n\nThe player finds themselves at the beginning of spring, but winter is coming. Food must be stored in your den if you are to survive the incoming onslaught of spectral frost.\n\nWander and explore dreamland in search of food, evade predators while also uncovering some mysteries.","x":-12445,"y":-22953,"width":405,"height":327},
		{"id":"fd45eef28da3f267","type":"text","text":"the game will be tile-based. tiles should support a texture (support for texture tiling), components for traversability, what type of tile it is (floor/wall), if it does damage when contacting, and dynamic creation/deletion as well as movement of tiles (although this can probably be done in a way like deleting the tile momentarily while creating an entity that looks like the tile)\n\nthe game will be real time and has a theme around emergent chaos where the creatures in the game have simple behavior but form more complex systems.\n\nthis game is set in a small chaotic maze where you play as a \"caroweasel\" that can store items in its cheeks. you must fill up your den with enough food to hibernate and move onto the next stage. creatures spawn gradually, with more difficult creatures spawning as time elapses. when the timer fully elapses, creatures called \"grues\" begin spawning, killing every creature in the maze.\n\nhow should i write creature behavior/ai? navigation meshes will have to be updated frequently (although godot 4 can store navigation meshes within tiles). \n\nthe solution should use a composition philosophy.","x":-11520,"y":-22953,"width":532,"height":520},
		{"id":"3bd773a033788c78","type":"text","text":"1. menu\n2. start game\n3. you are the caroweasel, bring food to your den before the shadows come\n4. run around and survive enemies\n5. deliver food back to den\n6. be near den when timer finishes\n7. when timer finishes, map goes dark and gruels spawn to hunt you down\n","x":-12005,"y":-22953,"width":460,"height":380},
		{"id":"f0988178bcdfc77a","type":"file","file":"assets/anthurium/photograph-of-a-big-red-flower-rafflesia-kemumu-on-the-rainforest-floor-m-3551524569.jpg","x":-9361,"y":-19873,"width":400,"height":301},
		{"id":"eb1b5be49c092154","type":"file","file":"assets/anthurium/154-OgreBattle64-176.jpg","x":-9361,"y":-19567,"width":400,"height":300},
		{"id":"52e8c52b0943cda1","type":"text","text":"graze\n\nactions:\n\n1. pathfind near a plant\n2. begin eating\n\t1. lower the plant's nutrition\n\t2. raise the animal's nutrition\n\t3. lower the animal's hunger","x":-17380,"y":-20648,"width":681,"height":318},
		{"id":"8a1c0af56ef4b92e","type":"text","text":"in `Goal`:\n\n```gdscript\nextends Node\nclass_name Goal\n\n@export var goal_name: String = \"base_goal\"\n@export var enabled: bool = true\n@export var completion_penalty: float = 0.5\n\nvar priority_penalty: float = 1.0\n@export var penalty_reduce_factor: float = 0.1\n\nfunc _process(delta: float) -> void:\n\tpriority_penalty = lerp(priority_penalty, 1.0, delta * penalty_reduce_factor)\n\n## evaluate how important this goal is at the current time given current internal state\nfunc evaluate_priority(brain: Brain) -> float:\n\treturn 0.0\n\n## calculates the intent for this goal\n## returns {direction: Vector2, action: String, target: Node2D}\nfunc generate_intent(brain: Brain) -> Intent:\n\tvar intent = Intent.new()\n\treturn intent\n\n```","x":-15358,"y":-21074,"width":740,"height":470},
		{"id":"cce009af7b261839","type":"text","text":"follow\n\npriority evaluation:\n1. search for nearby creatures (eyecomponent)\n2. set target as nearest creature\n3. priority is evaluated using a ratio between the creature's sympathy and the target's aggression\n\t1. higher self sympathy and lower target aggression make priority go up\n\nintent generation:\n1. get target as variable in goal\n2. \"follow\" action\n\nactions:\n1. look at target\n2. pathfind towards target with tolerance","x":-16859,"y":-21058,"width":560,"height":410},
		{"id":"64a97b71170ce443","type":"text","text":"attack_nearby\n\npriority evaluation:\n1. search for nearby creatures (eyecomponent)\n2. set target as nearest creature\n3. if a creature is within a specified distance, priority goes up\n\nintent generation:\n1. \"attack\" as action\n2. and post the target (stored as variable in goal)\n\nactions:\n1. look at target\n2. every interval, swipe\n\t1. activate hurtbox for a frame","x":-17380,"y":-21021,"width":521,"height":373},
		{"id":"a501cb4de5e3b0f3","type":"text","text":"in `MovementComponent`:\n```gdscript\nsignal goal_complete(intent: Intent)\n\nfunc register_action_handlers(executor: IntentExecutor):\n\texecutor.register_action(\"move_to_location\", _handle_move_to_location)\n\t\nfunc _handle_move_to_location(delta: float, intent: Intent) -> void:\n\t# move to a location (moving is done automatically every frame using move_direction)\n\t# once the location has been reached, signal goal_complete\n\tvar tolerance: float = intent.parameters.get(\"tolerance\", 5.0)\n\tvar direction: Vector2 = (intent.target_position - master_origin.position).normalized()\n\tset_intended_move_direction(direction)\n\t\n\tif master_origin.position.distance_squared_to(intent.target_position) < tolerance:\n\t\tgoal_complete.emit(intent)\n```","x":-16038,"y":-21074,"width":660,"height":340},
		{"id":"536b776cbc29daaa","type":"text","text":"creature personality traits\n\n**aggression**: affects hunting, attacking, territorial behavior\n**bravery**: affects fleeing, risk-taking, exploration\n**dominance**: affects leadership, pausing, submission\n**energy**: affects movement speed, activity level, rest\n**nervous**: affects fleeing, hiding, wariness\n**sympathy**: affects helping others, sharing, cooperation","x":-17419,"y":-21221,"width":560,"height":200},
		{"id":"8192cf326661696e","type":"text","text":"docile/friendly animals\n\nhow should they prioritize different behaviors in a neutral state?\nsay the environment is not hostile.\n\nfor a curious mouse-type creature, how should it prioritize following another creature versus wandering?\n\nCuriosityComponent?\n```gdscript\nvar boredom: float = 0.0\nvar curiosity: float = 0.0\n```","x":-16859,"y":-21331,"width":519,"height":273},
		{"id":"694ba4f1164c694d","type":"text","text":"**penalty system!**\ncomponent action functions will be able to emit a goal_complete signal which the brain will hook onto to place a temporary priority penalty on the current goal.\nif this works correctly, this means that some goals will be able to be refreshed without any absurd code workarounds.","x":-16038,"y":-21294,"width":380,"height":200},
		{"id":"67da6a8e4c9a12d0","type":"text","text":"in `Brain`:\n\n```gdscript\nfunc _on_goal_complete(intent: Intent) -> void:\n\tif intent == current_intent:\n\t\tcurrent_goal.priority_penalty -= current_goal.completion_penalty\n```","x":-15638,"y":-21254,"width":660,"height":160},
		{"id":"7b405a38ac309f80","type":"text","text":"```gdscript\nextends State\nclass_name WanderState\n\n@export var movement: MovementComponent\n@export var wall_avoidance: WallAvoidance\n@export var target_seeker: TargetSeeker\n@export var chase_state: State\n\nvar wander_timer: float = 0.0\nvar wander_direction: Vector2 = Vector2.ZERO\n\nfunc enter() -> void:\n\t_pick_new_wander_direction()\n\tif target_seeker:\n\t\ttarget_seeker.target_found.connect(_on_target_found)\n\t\t\nfunc update(delta: float) -> void:\n\twander_timer -= delta\n\tif wander_timer <= 0:\n\t\t_pick_new_wander_direction()\n\t\t\n\tvar steering = wander_direction\n\t\n\tif wall_avoidance:\n\t\tvar avoidance = wall_avoidance.get_avoidance_vector(\n\t\t\towner.global_position,\n\t\t\tmovement.velocity\n\t\t)\n\t\tsteering += avoidance\n\t\t\n\tif target_seeker:\n\t\tvar target = target_seeker.find_nearest_target(\n\t\t\towner.global_position,\n\t\t\tmovemtn.velocity.normalized()\n\t\t)\n\t\t\n\tmovement.set_desired_direction(steering)\n\t\nfunc physics_update(delta: float) -> void:\n\tmovement.physics_update(delta, owner)\n\t\nfunc exit() -> void:\n\tif target_seeker:\n\t\ttarget_seeker.target_found.disconnect(_on_target_found)\n\t\t\nfunc _pick_new_wander_direction() -> void:\n\twander_direction = Vector2.RIGHT.rotated(randf() * TAU)\n\twander_timer = randf_range(1.5, 4.0)\n\t\nfunc _on_target_found(target: Node2D) -> void:\n\tif chase_state:\n\t\tstate_machine.transition(chase_state)\n```","x":-16319,"y":-18972,"width":680,"height":1080},
		{"id":"d4ecb49fd8a5c8da","type":"text","text":"```gdscript\nextends Node\nclass_name TargetSeeker\n\nsignal target_found(target: Node2D)\nsignal target_lost()\n\n@export var detection_radius: float = 128.0\n@export var target_groups: Array[String] = [\"food\"]\n@export var vision_angle: float = 360.0\n@export var wall_collision_layer: int = 0\n\nvar current_target: Node2D = null\nvar last_known_position: Vector2\n\nfunc find_nearest_target(from_position: Vector2, facing_direction: Vector2) -> Node2D:\n\tvar best_target: Node2D = null\n\tvar best_distance: float = INF\n\t\n\tfor group_name in target_groups:\n\t\tvar potential_targets = owner.get_tree().get_nodes_in_group(group_name)\n\t\t\n\t\tfor target in potential_targets:\n\t\t\t# entity does not exist?\n\t\t\tif not is_instance_valid(target):\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\tvar to_target = target.global_position - from_position\n\t\t\tvar distance = to_target.length()\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t# too far away?\n\t\t\tif distance > detection_radius:\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t# outside vision cone?\n\t\t\tif vision_angle < 360.0:\n\t\t\t\tvar angle_to_target = facing_direction.angle_to(to_target)\n\t\t\t\tif abs(angle_to_target) > deg_to_rad(vision_angle) / 2.0):\n\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t# line of sight check; can we actually see it?\n\t\t\tif not has_line_of_sight(from_position, target.global_position):\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\tif distance < best_ddstance:\n\t\t\t\tbest_target = target\n\t\t\t\tbest_distance = distance\n\t\t\n\tif best_target != current_target:\n\t\tif current_target != null:\n\t\t\ttarget_lost.emit()\n\t\tif best_target != null:\n\t\t\ttarget_found.emit(best_target)\n\t\tcurrent_target = best_target\n\t\t\n\tif best_target:\n\t\tlast_known_position = best_target.global_position\n\t\t\n\treturn best_target\n\t\nfunc has_line_of_sight(from: Vector2, to: Vector2) -> bool:\n\tvar space_state = owner.get_world_2d().direct_space_state\n\t\n\tvar query = PhysicsRaycast2DQuery.create(from, to)\n\tquery.collision_mask = wall_collision_layer\n\tquery.collide_with_areas: false\n\tquery.collide_with_bodies = true\n\tquery.exclude = [owner]\n\t\n\tvar result = space_state.intersect_ray(query)\n\t\n\tif not result:\n\t\treturn true\n\t\t\n\tvar hit_distance = from.distance_to(result.position)\n\tvar target_distance = from.distance_to(to)\n\t\n\treturn hit_distance >= target_distance\n\t\nfunc get_direction_to_target(from_position: Vector2) -> Vector2:\n\tif curernt_target and is_instance_valid(current_target):\n\t\treturn (current_target.global_position - from_position).normalized()\n\telif last_known_position:\n\t\t# move toward last known position if we lost sight\n\t\treturn (last_known_position - from_position).normalized()\n\treturn Vector2.ZERO \n```","x":-17039,"y":-19572,"width":700,"height":1600},
		{"id":"11d044b71281c948","type":"text","text":"```gdscript\nextends Node\nclass_name WallAvoidance\n\n@export var raycast_distance: float = 32.0\n@export var avoidance_strength: float = 100.0\n@export var num_rays: int = 8\n@export var wall_collision_layer: int = 0\n\nfunc get_avoidance_vector(from_position: Vector2) -> Vector2:\n\tvar space_state = owner.get_world_2d().direct_space_state\n\tvar avoidance = Vector2.ZERO\n\t\n\t# cast rays in a circle around the creature\n\tfor i in range(num_rays):\n\t\tvar angle = (TAU / num_rays) * i\n\t\tvar direction = Vector2.RIGHT.rotated(angle)\n\t\t\n\t\tvar query = PhysicsRaycast2DQuery2D.create(\n\t\t\tfrom_position,\n\t\t\tfrom_position + direction * raycast_distance\n\t\t)\n\t\tquery.collision_mask = wall_collision_layer\n\t\tquery.collide_with_areas = false\n\t\tquery.collide_with_bodies = true\n\t\t\n\t\tvar result = space_state.intersect_ray(query)\n\t\t\n\t\tif result:\n\t\t\t# hit a wall!\n\t\t\t# calculate avoidance force\n\t\t\tvar hit_point = result.position\n\t\t\tvar distance = from_position.distance_to(hit_point)\n\t\t\t# stronger avoidance when closer to wall\n\t\t\tvar strength = 1.0 - (distance / raycast_distance)\n\t\t\tstrength = pow(strength, 2)\n\t\t\t# push away from the wall\n\t\t\tvar away_from_wall = (from_position - hit_point).normalized()\n\t\t\tavoidance += away_from_wall * strength\n\t\n\t# normalize and apply strength\n\tif avoidance.length() > 0:\n\t\tavoidance = avoidance.normalized() * avoidance_strength\n\t\t\n\treturn avoidance\n\t\n```\n\n\n\n","x":-17799,"y":-19572,"width":740,"height":880},
		{"id":"3d2ce95d97224c0c","type":"text","text":"```gdscript\nextends Node\nclass_name MovementComponent\n\n@export var max_speed: float = 100.0\n@export var acceleration: float = 500.0\n@export var friction: float = 800.0 # how fast it stopps\n@export var rotation_speed: float = 10.0 # for smooth turning\n\nvar velocity: Vector2 = Vector2.ZERO\nvar desired_direction: Vector2 = Vector2.ZERO\n\nfunc set_desired_direction(dir: Vector2) -> void:\n\tif dir.length() > 0:\n\t\tdesired_direction = dir.normalized()\n\telse:\n\t\tdesired_direction = Vector2.ZERo\n\t\nfunc physics_update(delta: float, body: CharacterBody2D) -> void:\n\tif desired_direction.length() > 0:\n\t\tvar target_velocity = desired_direction * max_speed\n\t\tvelocity = velocity.move_toward(target_velocity, acceleration * delta)\n\telse:\n\t\tvelocity = velocity.move_toward(Vector2.ZERO, friction * delta)\n\t\t\n\tbody.velocity = velocity\n\tbody.move_and_slide()\n\t\n\n\n```","x":-16319,"y":-19572,"width":680,"height":580},
		{"id":"4e469a37744930b0","type":"text","text":"as far as behavior goes, it would probably be the wisest to use state machines. they are the most versatile and fit with the composition philosophy i'm going for.\n\nstates would be their own godot 4 `Node` and depending on their function would only need access to certain components (or better yet, signals emitted by these components).\n\nfor example, if a state allowed for switching to a different state based on if the parent creature was harmed or not, the creature's `HealthComponent` would emit a signal if its health was lowered by cause of an attack. the state would hook onto that signal and if the signal was emitted, then the state would switch.\n\nstates should not hardcode their adjacent states; transitions should be exported in the godot inspector.\n\na `StateMachine` parent node would have all the `State` nodes as children.\n\n```gdscript\n# state example\n# note that the base class for State would probably have a state_machine variable in it\n\nvar state_machine: StateMachine\n@export var state_1: State\n@export var flee_state: State\n@export var health_component: HealthComponent\n\nfunc _ready() -> void:\n\tstate_machine = get_parent()\n\tif state_machine is not StateMachine:\n\t\tpush_error(\"Parent is not StateMachine!\")\n\t\t\n\tif health_component:\n\t\thealth_component.health_lost.connect(_on_health_lost)\n\nfunc enter() -> void:\n\t# stuff here\n\nfunc update(delta: float) -> void:\n\t# logic here\n\t\n\tif condition:\n\t\tstate_machine.transition(state_1)\n\nfunc physics_update(delta: float) -> void:\n\t# logic here which involves movement\n\t# this might not be necessary based on how i set things up\n\nfunc exit() -> void:\n\t# stuff here\n\nfunc _on_health_lost(amount: float, source: Node) -> void:\n\tif source.is_in_group(\"creature\"):\n\t\tstate_machine.transition(rage_state)\n\n```\n\n\n```gdscript\nextends Node\nclass_name StateMachine\n\nsignal state_switched(old_state: State, new_state: State)\n\nvar current_state: State\n\nfunc _process(delta: float) -> void:\n\tcurrent_state.update(delta)\n\t\nfunc _physics_process(delta: float) -> void:\n\tcurrent_state.physics_update(delta)\n\nfunc switch(new_state: State) -> void:\n\tcurrent_state.exit()\n\tstate_switched.emit(current_state, new_state)\n\tcurrent_state = new_state\n\tcurrent_state.enter()\n```","x":-18399,"y":-19572,"width":580,"height":1600},
		{
			"id":"9240d98c9c4c3b00",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Brain\n\nBrain (Node)\n1. has `Goal` nodes as children\n2. places `Goal` nodes in an array\n3. loops through all `Goal` nodes using `evaluate_priority()`\n4. sorts array based on priority values\n5. generates intent from highest priority goal every frame\n6. calls `execute_intent()` from `IntentExecutor`\n\nComponents map **action strings** to functions, which will then be called every frame by `execute_intent()` from the `IntentExecutor`\n\n```gdscript\nclass_name Brain\nextends Node\n\nsignal intent_changed(old_intent: Intent, new_intent: Intent)\nsignal goal_changed(old_goal_name: String, new_goal_name: String, new_priority: float)\n\n@export var creature: Node2D\n\n@export var personality: Dictionary[String, float] = {\n\t\"aggression\": 0.0,\n\t\"bravery\": 0.0,\n\t\"dominance\": 0.0,\n\t\"energy\": 0.0,\n\t\"nervous\": 0.0,\n\t\"sympathy\": 0.0\n}\n```\n\n```gdscript\n# goal management\nvar goals: Array[Goal] = []\nvar current_intent: Intent = null\nvar current_goal: Goal = null\n\n# memory system for persistent state\nvar memory: Dictionary = {}\n\n@export var priority_threshold: float = 1.2 # new goal must be this much higher to switch\n@export var min_goal_durations: float = 0.1 # minimum time before switching goals\n\nvar time_since_goal_change: float = 0.0\n\nfunc _ready() -> void:\n\tdetermine_personality()\n\t_gather_goals()\n\t\n\tcurrent_intent = Intent.new()\n\tcurrent_intent.action = \"idle\"\n\t\nfunc _process(delta: float) -> void:\n\ttime_since_goal_change += delta\n\t\n\tvar best_goal: Goal = _evaluate_goals()\n\t\n\tif _should_switch_goal(best_goal):\n\t\t_switch_to_goal(best_goal)\n```\n\n```gdscript\nfunc _gather_goals() -> void:\n\tgoals.clear()\n\tfor child in get_children():\n\t\tif child is Goal:\n\t\t\tgoals.append(child)\n\t\t\t\n\tif goals.is_empty():\n\t\tpush_warning(\"[Brain] No goals found for creature: %s\" % creature.name)\n\t\t\n\nfunc _evaluate_goals() -> Goal:\n\tvar best_goal: Goal = null\n\tvar highest_priority: float = -INF\n\t\n\tfor goal in goals:\n\t\tvar evaluated_priority = goal.evaluate_priority(self)\n\t\t\n\t\tif evaluated_priority > highest_priority:\n\t\t\thighest_priority = evaluated_priority\n\t\t\tbest_goal = goal\n\t\t\t\n\treturn best_goal\n```\n\n```gdscript\nfunc _should_switch_goal(new_goal: Goal) -> bool:\n\tif current_goal == null:\n\t\treturn new_goal != null\n\t\t\n\tif new_goal == null:\n\t\treturn false\n\t\t\n\tif new_goal == current_goal:\n\t\treturn false\n\t\t\n\tif time_since_goal_change < min_goal_duration:\n\t\treturn false\n\t\t\n\tvar current_priority = current_goal.evaluate_priority(self)\n\tvar new_priority = new_goal.evaluate_priority(self)\n\t\n\t# only switch if new goal is significantly better\n\treturn new_priority > current_priority + priority_threshold\n\t\n\t\nfunc _switch_to_goal(new_goal: Goal) -> void:\n\tvar old_intent = current_intent\n\tvar old_goal_name = current_goal.name if current_goal else \"none\"\n\t\n\tcurrent_goal = new_goal\n\ttime_since_goal_change = 0.0\n\t\n\tif new_goal == null:\n\t\tcurrent_intent = Intent.new()\n\t\tcurrent_intent.action = \"idle\"\n\t\tcurrent_intent.goal_name = \"idle\"\n\telse:\n\t\tcurrent_intent = new_goal.generate_intent(self)\n\t\tcurrent_intent.goal_name = new_goal.name\n\t\tcurrent_intent.priority = new_goal.evaluate_priority(self)\n\t\t\n\tgoal_changed.emit(old_goal_name, current_intent.goal_name, current_intent.priority)\n\tintent_changed.emit(old_intent, current_intent)\n```\n\n```gdscript\nfunc get_current_intent() -> Intent:\n\treturn current_intent\n\t\nfunc force_reevaluate() -> void:\n\tvar best_goal = _evaluate_goals()\n\tvar old_threshold = priority_threshold\n\tpriority_threshold = -INF\n\tif _should_switch_goal(best_goal):\n\t\t_switch_to_goal(best_goal)\n\tpriority_threshold = old_threshold\n\t\nfunc determine_personality() -> void:\n\tpersonality[\"aggression\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"bravery\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"dominance\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"energy\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"nervous\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"sympathy\"] = randf()\n```\n\n```gdscript\nfunc remember(key: String, value: Variant) -> void:\n\tmemory[key] = value\n\t\nfunc recall(key: String, default = null) -> Variant:\n\treturn memory.get(key, default)\n\t\nfunc forget(key: String) -> void:\n\tmemory.erase(key)\n\t\nfunc has_memory(key: String) -> bool:\n\treturn memory.has(key)\n\t\nfunc clear_memory() -> void:\n\tmemory.clear()\n\t\nfunc get_memory_keys() -> Array:\n\treturn memory.keys()\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{
				"shape":null,
				"border":null
			},
			"x":-18170,
			"y":-23651,
			"width":540,
			"height":2960
		},
		{"id":"f2ddb27e348c57c2","type":"text","text":"# IntentExecutor (ver2)\ncleaned up a bit\n\n```gdscript\nclass_name IntentExecutor\nextends Node\n\n@export var creature: Node2D\nvar previous_intent: Intent\nvar current_intent: Intent\nvar action_handlers: Dictionary = {} # String -> Callable\n\n￼func _ready():\n\t# components will register their own handlers\n\t_discover_component_handlers() \n\t\n\tvar brain: Brain = creature.get_node_or_null(\"Brain\")\n\tif brain:\n\t\tbrain.intent_changed.connect(_on_intent_changed)\n\t\t\nfunc _on_intent_changed(old_intent: Intent, new_intent: Intent) -> void:\n\t# when the brain switches intent, we need to change it here\n\t# we should also store the last intention\n\tcurrent_intent = new_intent\n\tprevious_intent = old_intent\n\t\n￼func _discover_component_handlers():\n\t# let components register their own action handlers\n\tfor child in creature.get_children()\n\tif child.has_method(\"register_intent_handlers\"):\n\t\tchild.register_intent_handlers(self)==-\n\t\t\nfunc register_action(action_name: String, handler: Callable):\n\t# public api for components to register handlers\n\taction_handlers[action_name] = handler\t\t\n\t\nfunc execute_intent(delta: float):\n\tif action_handlers.has(intent.action):\n\t\taction_handlers[intent.action].call(delta, current_intent)\n\telse:\n\t\t_try_component_dispatch(intent)\n\t\t\nfunc _try_component_dispatch(intent: CreatureIntent):\n\t# try to find a component that can handle this action\n\tfor child in creature.get_children():\n\t\tif child.has_method(\"handle_intent\"):\n\t\t\tif child.handle_intent(delta, intent):\n\t\t\t\treturn # component handled it\n```","x":-17370,"y":-22271,"width":640,"height":900,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"9d8e828ce90690cf","type":"text","text":"ai brain system\nA composition-based solution to creature intelligence in a top down environment/ecology.\n\nA creature is an object which can have multiple components attached.\nThese components can include simple things like a sprite, hitbox, hurtbox, and a physics collider.\nOther components are more custom and define parameters for the creature which have direct impact on their simulation.\nSome examples:\n* health component: stores a health and Max health value, emits signals when harmed or healed and when dead\n* hunger component: stores a hunger value, decrements hunger over time and emits a signal when the hunger value reaches 0 (starving)\n* eye component: takes in an area as a parameter and tracks different entity types, storing them as references in arrays. Stores a facing direction vector.\n* nutrition component: stores a nutrition value which changes when the creature eats or poops. Also stores a fat value increments when the creature eats while not hungry. Fat acts as a buffer so that the creature can live for longer if they are starved.\n* age component: stores an age value incremented over time which can have an effect on certain actions and movements. Stores a life expectancy value.\n* hand component: allows items to be picked up\n* movement component: stores an intended movement direction vector. Takes in a movement method module which defines custom movement logic if applicable. Normally this module interacts with a navigationagent node to post process paths.\n* action component: takes in an ability module (execute()). Stores values related to cast time, cooldown time, and charges.\n* brain component: has child nodes defining goals with priorities. Also stores and defines some personality values which may influence the priority of some goals.\n\nThe brain component is the most important in the context of giving creatures autonomy and personality.\n\nThe brain has goals as children. Every frame, the brain evaluates every goal’s priority using the goal’s custom algorithm. Then, the brain picks the goal with the highest evaluated priority and calls its update function.\n\nExample list of goals:\n* wander around while planting seeds occasionally\n* seek favorite fruit\n* hide and wait behind bushy plants\n* stalk creature\n* stay near walls\n* pause and watch\n* wander around\n* stay within a radius of an area\n* gather materials\n* hoard treasure\n* build a nest\n\nShould i have an update function inside the goal component itself or should i have the goal component return an intent data structure which other components can use? I think the right choice would be to have the goal component return an intent data structure rather than directly calling an update function. There's a couple reasons for doing this.\n\n* multiple goals can be expressed without duplicating movement logic\n* it's easier to add new goals in the case of adding simpler behaviors because it could be the case that the intent structure is all that's needed for a creature's components to handle behavior\n* it's easier to log and visualze what the creature wants to do vs what it's actually doing\n* easier to identify when goals are being overridden or failing\n\nNow i have to figure out what sort of parameters and data should fit into the intent data structure and how to translate those instructions into actual behaviors applied by the creature's components.\n\nFor something like \"build a nest\", the creature would need sufficient materials, and a target location to build at. So if there's not enough material near the target location then the build a nest goal would be vastly lower priority. Then this creature's other goals would be considered first; like perhaps a wander goal or a \"seek materials\" goal, then a \"drop material off\" goal with that nest target location in mind. For this goal and probably others, a consistent target location would need to be defined in memory (to prevent the creature from gathering materials in one spot and then attempting to build the nest in another, resulting in a behavioral soft lock).\n\nAdditionally, the brain comes with six personality modifiers which are initialized when the creature is first spawned.\n* aggression\n* bravery\n* dominance\n* energy\n* nervous\n* sympathy\n\nThese personality traits can act as modifiers for specific goals when applicable. For example, the \"pause and watch\" goal's priority could be modified by the 'dominance' trait. Higher levels of dominance mean that this creature is less likely to pause for a long amount of time.\n\nIt must be considered that every frame (or close to every frame) every creature's goal priorities are being calculated. This means that there is a chance that if these goals are not programmed correctly then creatures have the potential to flip between different goals every frame, causing twitchy movement or behavior.\n","x":-14640,"y":-23601,"width":980,"height":1580},
		{"id":"8e44cf4582dfb558","type":"text","text":"an example of a goal.\n\n```gdscript\nclass_name SeekShelterGoal\nextends Goal\n\n@export var shelter_detector: ShelterDetector\n@export var base_priority: float = 0.5\n\nfunc evaluate_priority(brain: Brain) -> float:\n\tvar world = WorldManager.get_world()\n\tvar is_raining = world.get(\"is_raining\")\n\tvar is_night = world.get(\"is_night\")\n\t\n\tif not is_raining and not is_night:\n\t\treturn 0.0\n\t\t\n\tif shelter_detector and shelter_detector.is_in_shelter():\n\t\treturn 0.0\n\t\t\n\tvar condition_multiplier = 1.0\n\tif is_raining:\n\t\tcondition_multiplier += 0.5\n\tif is_night:\n\t\tcondition_multiplier += 0.5\n\t\t\n\tvar nervous_modifier = 0.5 + brain.nervous\n\t\n\treturn base_priority * condition_multiplier * nervous_multiplier\n\t\n\t\nfunc generate_intent(brain: Brain) -> Intent:\n\tvar intent = Intent.new()\n\tvar eye = creature.get_node_or_null(\"EyeComponent\")\n\t\n\tif not eye:\n\t\treturn intent\n\t\t\n\tvar visible_shelters = eye.get_entities_of_type(\"shelter\")\n\t\n\tif visible_shelters.is_empty():\n\t\tintent.action = \"search_for_shelter\"\n\t\tintent.movement_style = \"urgent\"\n\t\treturn intent\n\t\t\n\tvar nearest_shelter = _find_closest(cerature, visible_shelters)\n\t\n\tintent.action = \"enter_shelter\"\n\tintent.target_entity = nearest_shelter\n\tintent.acceptable_distance = 10.0\n\tintent.movement_urgency = 0.8\n\t\n\treturn intent\n\t\n\nfunc _find_closest(creature: Node, entities: Array) -> Node:\n\treturn entities[0]\n```","x":-16670,"y":-23131,"width":700,"height":1040},
		{"id":"8cd779e8fb2e0eb4","type":"text","text":"# creature pack 3:\n\n**borega**\n- a colorful moth creature\n- flies overhead, charming creatures\n- leads charmed creatures into one area\n\n**totango**\n- wields percussion instruments\n- when enough creatures are nearby, starts a conga line\n- leads the parade until it is damaged\n\n**starman**\n- likes to be near trees\n- creates smaller versions of itself (they stun nearby creatures)\n- floats around aimlessly\n- does contact damage\n\n**tecton**\n- jumps long distances over terrain\n- jumps on top of creatures to catch them and eat them\n\n**waddler**\n- wanders around with its children\n- if the parent is killed, the children become ravenous\n\n**anhurgir**\n- demonic spirit that travels through walls\n- spits fire at creatures it doesn't like\n\n**wind wam**\n- creates directional gusts of wind\n- if the gust is powerful enough, it stuns the creature\n- spreads fire if there is any nearby\n\n**wind lord**\n- casts spells on **wind wams** to make their gusts more powerful\n- summons dangerous cyclones, causing entities to smash into each other\n\n**nutralon**\n- summons fruit\n- casts spells on fruit to make them bigger and more nutritive\n- wanders around aimlessly\n\n**mankey**\n- friends with other mankeys\n- throws stones at creatures it does not like\n- wants to be around other mankeys\n- picks up and roots **palmoids** in the ground, preventing them from moving\n\n**slumba**\n- likes treasure\n- picks a spot to designate its home\n- scampers around and brings treasure back to its home\n- attacks nearby creatures\n- mauls creatures near its trove","x":-6222,"y":-24014,"width":600,"height":1340},
		{"id":"99968e16ecb74240","type":"text","text":"# creature pack 5\n\n**puzzle**\n- hard as a rock\n- latches onto creatures or walls to form temporary structures\n\n**imp**\n- wanders around aimlessly\n- projects fake versions of itself\n- attacks nearby creatures\n\n**dungeon cube**\n- only travels in four cardinal directions\n- charges up energy, then slides until it hits a wall\n- destroys anything in its path\n\n**alchemite**\n- transforms items into any random object\n- wanders around aimlessly\n\n**mimic**\n- curious of other creatures\n- follows them around and copies their abilities\n\n**grub**\n- travels slowly\n- creates sludge on the ground that makes creatures slow down\n\n**gloob**\n- hops one tile at a time\n- creates lightweight breakable terrain when it hops\n\n**poltergeist**\n- shuffles terrain around itself (including all entities on these tiles)\n- floats around, passing through hard terrain\n- likes being near other creatures\n\n**clone**\n- wanders around aimlessly\n- attacks nearby creatures\n- clones itself when harmed, halving its current health\n\n**cultist**\n- shoots explosive fireballs at a target\n- fireballs can travel over terrain\n- does not move, teleports nearby other creatures\n\n**kisse**\n- slurps up nearby projectiles and spits them back to their origin\n- likes being in open spaces or in water","x":-4962,"y":-24014,"width":540,"height":1340},
		{"id":"f47c88c6fe525004","type":"text","text":"# creature pack 6\n\n**bounce blob**\n- a round bouncy slime creature\n- likes being around walls\n- reacts dramatically to other creatures bumping into it\n- bounces off of walls\n- grows larger with every bounce until it bursts into smaller blobs\n\n**palmoid**\n- plantlike creature\n- throws coconuts at nearby creatures\n- coconuts are fruits and can be eaten\n- moves very slowly\n\n**fernoid**\n- plantlike creature\n- likes to be near other **fernoids**\n- creatures next to fernoids are invisible and undetectable\n- regularly drops edible leaves\n\n**spectroid**\n- can creep through terrain\n- occasionally drops edible spectral flowers\n- spectral flowers allow creatures to pass through walls\n\n**tarrite**\n- grows crystals which reflect projectiles\n- crystals also react chaotically to contact damage\n- plants crystals in the ground occasionally\n\n**spike ball**\n- rolls around causing massive contact damage\n- damage is higher the faster it goes\n- its velocity can only be increased\n- if it runs into a wall at a specific velocity it shatters\n\n**blossom**\n- tangles creatures up in vines\n- if creatures are tangled up for long enough, they are dragged into the soil\n- this creates a random plantlike creature\n\n**bomba**\n- absorbs energy from fire\n- when damaged, it explodes using its built up energy\n- can build up energy infinitely\n\n**gnome**\n- wants to be around plantlike creatures\n- waters plantlike creatures for a chance to duplicate them\n\n**puff wizard**\n- gets upset when creatures are harmed\n- runs near just harmed creatures\n- grows mushrooms which expel healing spores","x":-4382,"y":-24014,"width":640,"height":1340},
		{"id":"be3f66f7cd7775cf","type":"text","text":"# creature pack 7\n\n**architect**\n- creates lines of walls nearby other creatures\n\n**popbug**\n- infests walls\n- slowly creates more **popbugs** which infest adjacent walls\n- pop out of walls when destroyed\n- attack nearby creatures\n- can infest the **stone**\n\n**door master**\n- creates intradimensional doors which lead to other areas\n\n**keyman**\n- sometimes pops out of doors when used\n- runs away, creating treasure\n- attacks nearby creatures\n\n**scavenger**\n- a more complex being\n- has a designated home belonging to other scavengers\n- go out in parties hunting or looking for treasure\n- can be traded with for their exotic crafts\n\n**warden** (*large*)\n- can alter reality to get to where it wants\n- changes tiles to dramatically different things\n- hunts **door masters**\n- hostile to creatures that provoke it\n\n**bubbler**\n- wanders around aimlessly\n- blows bubbles which can catch creatures\n- bubbles are highly affected by wind\n- bubbles transport creatures over terrain, but eventually pop\n\n**spin wheel**\n- like the **dungeon cube**, but only travels in diagonals\n\n**plant wizard**\n- casts spells on creatures to turn them plantlike\n- wanders around aimlessly\n- roots creatures occasionally","x":-3702,"y":-24014,"width":520,"height":1340},
		{"id":"8ed7695916456101","type":"text","text":"# creature pack 4:\n\n\n**cat**\n- naps in corners\n- gets agitated if awoken suddenly\n- scratches and runs away rapidly\n\n**blaze**\n- has orbiting flame pillars\n- shoots its pillars at creatures\n- catches the environment on fire\n\n**pyre**\n- continuously on fire\n- moves quickly but pauses often\n- rarely shoots a wave of flame\n\n**bongo** (*large*)\n- beats on its drum, creating shockwaves\n- gets angry when hungry, drumming faster\n- shockwaves spread fire if there is any nearby\n\n**frozer**\n- causes nearby tiles to freeze, making them slippery\n- throws snowballs at creatures\n- if cold enough, freezes creatures and items solid\n\n**bumble**\n- stomps around, damaging those near it\n- exhales a blizzard, freezing the area in front of it\n- breathes on **frozers**, powering them up and making their cold colder\n\n**slushy**\n- ice tornado spirit\n- shoots ice shards rapidly and plants them in walls\n- makes terrain brittle\n\n**gordon** (*large*)\n- slowly rolls around\n- when nearby a creature it attempts to grab it\n- grabbed creatures are then swallowed\n- if **gordon** is killed, all swallowed creatures burst out\n\n**slick**\n- rides around on its board\n- spreads oil on the ground which can stick itself to creatures\n- makes fire do more damage and last longer\n- attacks nearby creatures\n\n**kernel**\n- waddles around\n- if lit on fire, it will burst into several popped corns\n- popped corns will jump and run frantically around\n- popped corns attack nearby enemies\n- popped corns eventually burst, causing a small explosion","x":-5582,"y":-24014,"width":580,"height":1340},
		{"id":"0b8abbd04cfc4018","type":"file","file":"assets/4eecb63e70de0bc549ebf400cd797fa1.gif","x":-6581,"y":-17993,"width":345,"height":460},
		{"id":"807a7d4d9587c5f1","type":"text","text":"Components can handle actions by implementing `register_intent_handlers()`.\nThese functions should utilize the information given in `CreatureIntent` to properly\nexample:\n```gdscript\nclass_name NutritionComponent\nextends Node\n\nvar nutrition: float = 100.0\nvar max_nutrition: float = 100.0\nvar fat: float = 0.0\n\nfunc register_event_handlers(executor: IntentExecutor):\n\texecutor.register_action(\"eat\", _handle_eat)\n\texecutor.register_action(\"poop\", _handle_poop)\n\t# i be consuming all the poop that i be pooping\n\t\nfunc _handle_eat(delta, intent: Intent):\n\tpass\n\t\nfunc _handle_poop(delta, intent: Intent):\n\tpass\n```","x":-16610,"y":-22041,"width":540,"height":470},
		{"id":"b7e3b9915efd0e3a","type":"text","text":"# Intent\nPossible proposal for `Intent` class.\nComponents can use this framework for to register actions which are the basis of executing behavior based on a goal->intent.\n```gdscript\nclass_name Intent\nextends Resource\n\nvar action: String = \"idle\"\nvar priority: float = 0.0\n\nvar target_position: Vector2\nvar target_entity: Node\nvar target_entities: Array[Node]\n\nvar movement_style: String = \"default\"\nvar acceptable_distance_to_target: float = 10.0\nvar movement_urgency: float = 0.5\n\nvar look_target: Variant = null\n\nvar parameters: Dictionary = {}\n\nvar memory_key: String = \"\"\nvar goal_name: String = \"\"\nvar cancel_if: Array[String] = []\n```","x":-15870,"y":-22731,"width":424,"height":567,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"00d321f815867cf8","type":"text","text":"Examples on usage\n\n```gdscript\nintent.action = \"move_to\"\nintent.target_position = some_position\nintent.acceptable_distance = 20.0\n```\n\n```gdscript\nintent.action = \"wait\"\nintent.parameters = {\n\t\"duration\": 5.0\n}\n```\n\n```gdscript\nintent.action = \"eat\"\nintent.target_entity = target_object\nintent.acceptable_distance = 15.0\n```\n\n```gdscript\nintent.action = \"gather_materials\"\nintent.target_position = material_spawn_area.global_position\nintent.parameters = {\n\t\"material_type\": \"stick\",\n\t\"collect_amount\": 5,\n\t\"drop_off_location\": nest_location,\n}\n```","x":-15446,"y":-22731,"width":460,"height":567,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"919a3bb569407e4d","type":"text","text":"# Goal\n```gdscript\nclass_name Goal\nextends Node\n\nfunc evaluate_priority(brain: Brain) -> float:\n\treturn 0.0\n\t\nfunc generate_intent(brain: Brain) -> Intent:\n\tvar intent = Intent.new()\n\treturn intent\n```","x":-17269,"y":-22691,"width":438,"height":260},
		{"id":"0a113eed4a7cc760","type":"text","text":"**pellet**\n\na projectile works differently to a character.\nprojectiles have a hitbox and a hurtbox.\nsome projectiles will take damage or die when their hurtbox is contacted.\n\nit's a bit fucked up because collision and damage is handled on the side of the victim. the victim takes damage when their hitbox comes in contact with a hurtbox.\n\nso how do i add exceptions so that the originator of a pellet doesn't take damage?\n\na FriendComponent?\n\nso hurtbox -> hitbox -> healthcomponent (take_damage)\n\nokay so i could just add a FriendComponent to the salmon, then when a pellet needs to be spawned, then add it to a list in the friendcomponent. if the friend's hurtbox touches the salmon's hitbox, then nothing should happen since it's in the list.\n\nthere should be functions to add and remove friends. if a friend needs to be retrieved, then all invalid instances should be removed from the list first.","x":-6237,"y":-20595,"width":640,"height":620},
		{"id":"94bbe267d1f7db6a","type":"text","text":"**rud**\n\nhops strategically\n> not sure what this means\n> im sure the rud wants to stay within a certain radius of a water tile, but other than that i think the rud will also just hop around in random directions.\n> i don't think the rud can jump over walls.\n\neats salmon\n> perhaps create a hunger component and then use that; when under a threshold the rud hunts.\n> when hunting, another threshold will have to be surpassed to calm the rud down.\n> or maybe when there's a nearby salmon, there's a percent chance each second that the rud decides to hunt it. that's probably a better idea. this could be a component which emits a signal\n\ncauses shockwaves when it hops\n> a simple hurtbox and particle. use a signal to connect this to when the frog \"lands\" after hopping.","x":-5357,"y":-20995,"width":540,"height":470},
		{"id":"f536f835e5ec71d8","type":"text","text":"**salmon**\n\nflops around aimlessly\n> perhaps figure out some magic involving shadows; the fish's sprite should hop and bounce when it moves.\n\nshoots pellets at nearby creatures\n> this is easy, just have to make a pellet object and add a hurtbox to it. it shouldn't collide with terrain. let's just make this a characterbody2d.\n> targets can be any creature.\n\nlikes being in water\n> this can come later, involves giving custom properties to tiles. maybe consider buying tilesetter for texturing?\n> maybe the salmon can behave differently in the water","x":-5357,"y":-21395,"width":540,"height":380},
		{"id":"4a230eed43f25a89","type":"text","text":"**bitwit**\n\nis knocked around easily\n> i think i might need to make a knockback component for this. something that basically disables any sort of movement and pretty much changes the creature into a rigidbody that slides around.\n> any time the bitwit is collided into at a threshold speed, this state should be switched into for a period of time\n\nfollows creatures around\n> wanders around except for when it decides to pick a target creature to follow around closely. this is probably on interval or a random chance every second.\n> bitwits are more likely to choose targets that have more bitwits already following.\n> this would just be a call to the targetseeker and then a state switch to get the target's position and pathfind towards that.\n\nbitwits are small\n> they are a lot smaller than the average size creature (16px), i'm thinking probably 8px small","x":-4797,"y":-21395,"width":540,"height":470},
		{"id":"167b9cdbef28029d","type":"text","text":"**floroid**\n\ncompanion fruit\n> for now, we can have this just be eaten instantly, there will need to be animations and sound later\n> lateron also we can add in stuff like stages and graphics and stuff\n\ndigs underground\n> basically this would just be hiding the sprite or changing it to something different and also disabling its hitbox and collision box.\n> maybe increase the movement speed or have it use a differnet movement function while underground\n> particles and fun stuff later\n\ncomes up occasionally to drop a fruit\n> this can just be on a timer, like a range or something\n> TODO: add a component for a timer with a range\n\ndamages walls it digs under\n> this is more tricky and involves mapping a pixel coordinate position to a tile unit position.\n> i've made systems before that give tiles properties so all i would have to do is store these properties in a data structure using the tile unit position as a key.\n> translate the coordinate position into the tile position and use that as the key to get the cell at that coordinate, then update its statistics.\n> any changes to the statistics will be reflected visually by the tilemaplayer. no changes are to be made to the collision boxes or navigation meshes of any tiles (it won't be necessary)\n\n","x":-5837,"y":-21395,"width":460,"height":720},
		{"id":"3766a7824e732e7e","type":"text","text":"creature state loops\n\n**cow**\npathfindwander --(hunger)--> pathfindwanderandseek --(found)--> chasetarget --(vicinity)--> eat --(finished)--> pathfindwander\n\n**imp**\npathfindwander --(vicinity)--> standstillandattack --(not in vicinity)--> pathfindwander\n\n**plopp**\npathfindwander --(interval)--> plop --(finished)--> pathfindwander\n\n**stone**\npathfindwanderpreferwalls\n\n**salmon**\npathfindwanderpreferwater --(interval)--> pathfindwanderandseek --(found)--> standstillandattack --(done)--> pathfindwanderpreferwater\n\n**rud**\npathfindwanderpreferwater --(hunger)--> pathfindwanderandseek --(found)--> chasetarget --(vicinity)--> eat --(finished)--> pathfindwanderpreferwater\n\n**bitwit**\npathfindwander --(interval)--> pathfindwanderandseek --(vicinity)--> idle","x":-7037,"y":-21365,"width":1120,"height":660},
		{"id":"7ed5d186a3c410a0","type":"file","file":"assets/original_025070e5d893cecc740d90dfec23cf93.gif","x":-6236,"y":-17993,"width":564,"height":460},
		{"id":"e2861cd28dd27752","type":"text","text":"hopper\nbean moth\njack a tack\npolyp\nsugar star plum jam\nchar broil\nchomper\ndawg\nswag bug\nkeyman\nflorgon\npopbug\ndreamer\nglory lord\nchum\nslumlord\nparagon\neminence\nrubicon\nbuddy baby bug dog","x":-7222,"y":-22574,"width":220,"height":560},
		{"id":"0fe1f64f0978ebe6","type":"text","text":"Aragon Ramorey\nAnamis Kan\nRageon Tamarin\nWollom Nol\nJoe Street\nOolivey Blond\nHargoid Max\nBarflam Inga\nNeal Shol\nHorotious Nalaimian\nMalloch Jumping\nBarnable Chimney\nYodeler\n","x":-6962,"y":-22574,"width":320,"height":420},
		{"id":"7656b5cb73cb303d","type":"text","text":"chungus\npibble x bape\ni am pibble wash my bellay\nchipi chipi chapa\nskeleton running eyes\nRAAAUUGH skeleton banging shield\nskeletons judging berserk\nagartha yakub\nhm hm hm dog\nhenry ayveries\nson im crine\nfahhhh","x":-6602,"y":-22574,"width":380,"height":480},
		{"id":"995a7243d87d3a0a","type":"text","text":"# creature pack 1:\n\n**plopp**\n- creates edible orbs\n- wanders around aimlessly\n- dances occasionally, spitting more orbs\n\n**moo**\n- wanders around aimlessly\n- eats orbs\n- flees from threats\n\n**imp**\n- wanders around\n- likes to be near walls\n- attacks nearby creatures\n\n**floroid**\n- plantlike creature\n- dies in one hit\n- digs underground unseen\n- comes up occasionally to drop a fruit of its type\n- damages walls it digs under\n\n**stone**\n- hard as a rock\n- moves slowly\n- wanders around\n- collides with creatures like terrain\n- likes to be near walls\n- likes to be near other stones\n\n**salmon**\n- flops around aimlessly\n- shoots pellets at nearby creatures\n- likes being in water\n\n**rud**\n- hops strategically\n- eats salmon\n- causes shockwaves when it hops\n\n**bitwit**\n- friendly puffball\n- is knocked around easily\n- follows creatures around\n\n**hoary**\n- designates an area as 'his lawn'\n- attacks any creature on his lawn\n- likes the **gnome**\n\n**grue**\n- comes out only at night\n- ruthlessly hunts down other creatures\n\n","x":-7282,"y":-24014,"width":460,"height":1340},
		{"id":"34ec2301994781a5","type":"text","text":"# creature pack 2:\n\n**tarantorra**\n- creates a home web\n- guards its web until hungry\n- stalks and pounces on prey and webs them up\n- brings prey back to its home\n\n**carpo**\n- eats a fruit then becomes a big version of it\n- when hit it creates more fruits\n\n**ceefor**\n- sits in an area until damaged\n- when harmed, it runs around panicked\n- after a while it detonates in a large explosion\n\n**runbone**\n- dashes quickly across the screen\n- stuns nearby creatures\n- damages creatures it runs over\n\n**spatuler**\n- drills through walls\n- searches for valuables and treasure\n- likes **stone** creatures and wants to breed them\n\n**kori**\n- moves quickly around\n- hangs around its nest\n- quickly grabs food and brings them back to its nest\n- feeds its nested children\n- attacks nearby creatures\n\n**hog**\n- travels in packs with other hogs\n- follows the most dominant hog\n- prefers hunting *large* creatures\n\n**giant worm** (*large*)\n- multiple body segments which trail behind its head\n- eats creatures in its path\n- digs through walls easily\n\n**mooer** (*large*)\n- a massive cow which formed from too many cows being in one area\n- wanders around aimlessly\n- eats grass (and sometimes creatures whole)\n- flees from threats\n- regularly produces cheese\n\n**rage beast** (*large*)\n- is dormant until too many creatures are nearby\n- goes into a rampage until it finds a quiet area\n- attacks indiscriminately","x":-6782,"y":-24014,"width":520,"height":1340},
		{"id":"6529d1de046bd420","type":"file","file":"assets/03aca7785e04b8e64b53a93098a54ea6.gif","x":-7081,"y":-17993,"width":500,"height":460},
		{"id":"12fcd0b5503179f4","type":"file","file":"assets/link/tumblr_ok5w9ve6tm1tsp14vo3_500-3713063197.gif","x":-7701,"y":-17891,"width":400,"height":320},
		{"id":"4a04a95aba69295d","type":"file","file":"assets/a8a7dcec34fd2b1cbe978486706f5a9a.gif","x":-7081,"y":-18400,"width":844,"height":407},
		{"id":"13a795711fdab5d4","type":"text","text":"```gdscript\nextends State\nclass_name PathfindWanderState\n\n@export var movement: MovementComponent\n@export var wall_avoidance: WallAvoidance\n@export var target_seeker: TargetSeeker\n@export var navigation_agent: NavigationAgent2D\n\n@export var animator: SpriteAnimator\n@export var facing: FacingComponent\n\n@export_group(\"States\")\n@export var chase_state: State\n@export var idle_state: State\n@export_group(\"Variables\")\n\n@export var timer_length: float = 5.0\nvar wander_timer: float = 0.0\nvar wander_direction: Vector2 = Vector2.ZERO\n@export var wander_radius: float = 250.0\n\n\nsignal picked_new_path(target_position: Vector2)\nsignal found_target(target: Node2D)\nsignal interrupted()\n\nfunc enter() -> void:\n\t_pick_new_pathfinding_location(owner.position)\n\tif target_seeker:\n\t\ttarget_seeker.target_found.connect(_on_target_found)\n\t\t\n\tif navigation_agent:\n\t\tnavigation_agent.navigation_finished.connect(_on_navigation_finished)\n\t\t\n\tinterrupted.connect(_decide_if_idle)\n\t\n\tfound_target.connect(_on_target_found)\n\t\n\tif animator:\n\t\tanimator.load_animation(\"walk\")\n\t\t\nfunc update(delta: float) -> void:\n\tvar old_wander_direction: Vector2 = wander_direction\n\twander_timer -= delta\n\tif wander_timer <= 0:\n\t\tinterrupted.emit()\n\t\t_pick_new_pathfinding_location(owner.position)\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\nfunc physics_update(delta: float) -> void:\n\tvar next_path_position: Vector2 = navigation_agent.get_next_path_position()\n\twander_direction = (next_path_position - owner.global_position).normalized()\n\tvar steering = wander_direction\n\t\n\t\n\tif wall_avoidance:\n\t\tvar avoidance = wall_avoidance.get_avoidance_vector(owner.global_position)\n\t\tsteering += avoidance\n\t\t\n\tif target_seeker:\n\t\tvar target = target_seeker.find_nearest_target(\n\t\t\towner.global_position,\n\t\t\tmovement.velocity.normalized()\n\t\t)\n\t\t\n\t\tif target:\n\t\t\tfound_target.emit(target)\n\t\t\n\tmovement.set_desired_direction(steering)\n\t\n\tmovement.physics_update(delta, owner)\n\t\n\tif animator:\n\t\tanimator.update_animation(delta, movement.velocity.length() * 0.2)\n\t\t\n\tif facing:\n\t\tfacing.change_direction(steering)\n\nfunc exit() -> void:\n\tif target_seeker:\n\t\ttarget_seeker.target_found.disconnect(_on_target_found)\n\t\t\n\tif navigation_agent:\n\t\tnavigation_agent.navigation_finished.disconnect(_on_navigation_finished)\n\t\t\n\tinterrupted.disconnect(_decide_if_idle)\n\t\n\tfound_target.disconnect(_on_target_found)\n\t\t\nfunc _pick_new_pathfinding_location(origin: Vector2) -> void:\n\tvar angle: float = randf() * TAU\n\tvar distance = randf() * wander_radius\n\tvar target_position: Vector2 = origin + Vector2(cos(angle), sin(angle)) * distance\n\tnavigation_agent.set_target_position(target_position)\n\twander_timer = timer_length\n\tpicked_new_path.emit(target_position)\n\t\nfunc _on_navigation_finished() -> void:\n\tinterrupted.emit()\n\t_pick_new_pathfinding_location(owner.position)\n\nfunc _on_target_found(target: Node2D) -> void:\n\tif chase_state:\n\t\tstate_machine.switch(chase_state)\n\n\nfunc _decide_if_idle() -> void:\n\tvar chance: float = 0.3\n\tif randf() < 0.3:\n\t\tstate_machine.switch(idle_state)\n\n```\n\nthis is my basic pathfinding and wandering script. it could be necessary to alter the `_pick_new_pathfinding_location()` function to either avoid or pick a point near walls. there could be a distance calculation and if the distance is not satisfactory, another point would be generated and chosen.\n\nwalls are on collision layer 1, so i'd have to make sure that the raycasts (or however way the walls are detected) are on collision mask 1.","x":-8654,"y":-22937,"width":693,"height":2160},
		{"id":"d36d35cbc08b8f5d","type":"text","text":"# StateComponent\n(presentation)\nHow the creature appears while acting\n","x":-9890,"y":-26052,"width":400,"height":236},
		{"id":"6968a814f8950b3d","type":"text","text":"# Components\nThe creature's actual components will allow the creature to perform actions and movement to complete their goals\n- HealthComponent\n- NutritionComponent\n- MovementComponent\n- EyeComponent\n...to name a few","x":-9890,"y":-26440,"width":320,"height":284},
		{"id":"b582f3e6b534e552","type":"text","text":"what's the best way of making creatures aware of how near they are to walls?\n\n(probably raycasting)\n\nonce they have data representing their vicinity to walls, how do i influence the creature's movement to prefer spots closer to walls?\n\nhow do i define \"closer to walls\"?\n\n```gdscript\nextends Node\nclass_name MovementComponent\n\n@export var max_speed: float = 100.0\n@export var acceleration: float = 500.0\n@export var friction: float = 800.0 # how fast it stopps\n@export var rotation_speed: float = 10.0 # for smooth turning\n\n\nvar velocity: Vector2 = Vector2.ZERO\nvar desired_direction: Vector2 = Vector2.ZERO\n\nsignal started_moving(direction: Vector2)\nsignal stopped_moving()\nsignal changed_direction(old_direction: Vector2, new_direction: Vector2)\n\n\nvar moving: bool = false\n\nfunc set_desired_direction(dir: Vector2) -> void:\n\tif dir.length() > 0:\n\t\tdesired_direction = dir.normalized()\n\telse:\n\t\tdesired_direction = Vector2.ZERO\n\t\nfunc physics_update(delta: float, body: CharacterBody2D) -> void:\n\tmovement_function(delta, body)\n\t\t\n\tdetect_active_movement()\n\t\n\tbody.move_and_slide()\n\t\nfunc movement_function(delta: float, body: CharacterBody2D) -> void:\n\tif desired_direction.length() > 0:\n\t\tvar target_velocity = desired_direction * max_speed\n\t\tvelocity = velocity.move_toward(target_velocity, acceleration * delta)\n\telse:\n\t\tvelocity = velocity.move_toward(Vector2.ZERO, friction * delta)\n\tbody.velocity = velocity\n\t\t\nfunc detect_active_movement() -> void:\n\tif abs(velocity.x) < 0.05 or abs(velocity.y) < 0.05:\n\t\tif moving:\n\t\t\tstopped_moving.emit()\n\t\tmoving = false\n\telse:\n\t\tif not moving:\n\t\t\tstarted_moving.emit(velocity.normalized())\n\t\tmoving = true \n\t\t\n\t\n\n```\n\nthis is the default movement component, but it is easy to overload the movement function to compute velocity in different ways.\n\nit might also be necessary to do post processing on pathfinding!\n\n","x":-9560,"y":-22300,"width":780,"height":1220},
		{"id":"d0ce50e1682adec4","type":"file","file":"assets/b9a8afc838c0c26dcd4b72884d38ac30.jpg","x":-7081,"y":-17533,"width":400,"height":240},
		{"id":"ece270abc95f17b8","type":"text","text":"how to make creatures move? this solution should be as performant as possible, as efficient as possible.\n\nmy options:\n- direct steering (move away/toward the target)\n- raycasting\n- local tile queries (whats in the 8 tiles adjacent)\n- pathfinding using BFS or A*\n\nwhen creatures are wandering/searching, it is appropriate to use behaviors like local tile queries or raycasting.\n\ncreatures should avoid moving into walls, and when in tight hallways (a 1 tile wide hallway), creatures should position themselves in the center of the hallway. creatures should never brush into corners; when met with a corner, a creature should position itself so that it can travel straight down the new path before turning (sharp steering). ideally, a creature's physics collider should never collide with a wall when moving normally (wandering or pathing).\n\nthe only reason a creature would need to use pathfinding was if it stored a location in memory and needed to path to that coordinate location.\n\ninstead of using nav meshes (in the case of godot, storing a unique navmesh for each tile) it can be considered using a cached array of values from some search algorithm. i'm concerned of creatures getting lost in a maze, so a search algorithm would be helpful to get a path to a specific location when applicable.","x":-10340,"y":-22976,"width":720,"height":700},
		{"id":"f0fdd5298e0ce7de","type":"text","text":"movement is not locked to a grid; creatures can move wherever they please.\nhow does *a link to the past* handle enemy ai, movement, behavior, etc?\n\nmy creatures really have only two types of movement behavior right now:\n- wandering, attacking, searching (no specific location in mind)\n- pursuing, following, navigating (a specific coordinate is used)\n\ncreatures when wandering/searching:\n- raycasting\n\t- get distance from walls and avoid contacting them\n\t- get line of sight for threats, food, objects of interest\n- manipulate steering direction based on raycast output\n\ncreatures when navigating to specific location\n- pathfinding\n\t- get nodes along path\n\t- ensure nodes consider making a sharp angle when in a tight hallway only, otherwise preserve natural-looking movement (this can probably be done in post-processing of navigation nodes)\n- raycasting\n\t- get distance from walls and avoid contacting them\n- manipulate steering direction based on raycast and pathfind output\n\nin godot, navigation meshes can be stored per tile. so creating, destroying, modifying, or moving tiles dynamically updates the navigation map. i'm not sure how performant this is though.","x":-9590,"y":-22976,"width":580,"height":600},
		{"id":"0f4cf88f942bc817","type":"text","text":"# GoalComponent\n(decision-making)\nONLY describes intent\n```gdscript\nvar goal: Dictionary = {\n\t\"direction\": Vector2,\n\t\"action\": String,\n\t\"target\", Node2D\n}\n```\n\nEach goal has a custom `evaluate_priority()` function which is called every frame.\nNaturally, each goal also has a priority which influences when it will be picked from a brain's stack of goals.\nGoals can be split into basic want modules:\n- I want food\n- I want safety\n- I want treasure\netc.\n","x":-10450,"y":-26318,"width":400,"height":500},
		{"id":"8ec62334c73e9710","type":"text","text":"# BrainModule\nKeeps a stack of GoalComponents, organizes and calls their functions to give creatures a goal.\nEncourages emergent behavior using the priority-based goal system and personality parameters.","x":-11000,"y":-26156,"width":430,"height":176},
		{"id":"ced146fe3fd821bb","type":"text","text":"```gdscript\nclass_name Brain\nextends Node\n\nsignal intent_changed(old_intent: Intent, new_intent: Intent)\nsignal goal_changed(old_goal_name: String, new_goal_name: String, new_priority: float)\n\n@export var creature: Node2D\n\n@export var personality: Dictionary[String, float] = {\n\t\"aggression\": 0.0,\n\t\"bravery\": 0.0,\n\t\"dominance\": 0.0,\n\t\"energy\": 0.0,\n\t\"nervous\": 0.0,\n\t\"sympathy\": 0.0\n}\n\n# goal management\nvar goals: Array[Goal] = []\nvar current_intent: Intent = null\nvar current_goal: Goal = null\n\n# memory system for persistent state\nvar memory: Dictionary = {}\n\n@export var priority_threshold: float = 1.2 # new goal must be this much higher to switch\n@export var min_goal_durations: float = 0.1 # minimum time before switching goals\n\nvar time_since_goal_change: float = 0.0\n\nfunc _ready() -> void:\n\tdetermine_personality()\n\t_gather_goals()\n\t\n\tcurrent_intent = Intent.new()\n\tcurrent_intent.action = \"idle\"\n\t\nfunc _process(delta: float) -> void:\n\ttime_since_goal_change += delta\n\t\n\tvar best_goal: Goal = _evaluate_goals()\n\t\n\tif _should_switch_goal(best_goal):\n\t\t_switch_to_goal(best_goal)\n\t\nfunc _gather_goals() -> void:\n\tgoals.clear()\n\tfor child in get_children():\n\t\tif child is Goal:\n\t\t\tgoals.append(child)\n\t\t\t\n\tif goals.is_empty():\n\t\tpush_warning(\"[Brain] No goals found for creature: %s\" % creature.name)\n\t\t\n\nfunc _evaluate_goals() -> Goal:\n\tvar best_goal: Goal = null\n\tvar highest_priority: float = -INF\n\t\n\tfor goal in goals:\n\t\tvar evaluated_priority = goal.evaluate_priority(self)\n\t\t\n\t\tif evaluated_priority > highest_priority:\n\t\t\thighest_priority = evaluated_priority\n\t\t\tbest_goal = goal\n\t\t\t\n\treturn best_goal\n\t\nfunc _should_switch_goal(new_goal: Goal) -> bool:\n\tif current_goal == null:\n\t\treturn new_goal != null\n\t\t\n\tif new_goal == null:\n\t\treturn false\n\t\t\n\tif new_goal == current_goal:\n\t\treturn false\n\t\t\n\tif time_since_goal_change < min_goal_duration:\n\t\treturn false\n\t\t\n\tvar current_priority = current_goal.evaluate_priority(self)\n\tvar new_priority = new_goal.evaluate_priority(self)\n\t\n\t# only switch if new goal is significantly better\n\treturn new_priority > current_priority + priority_threshold\n\t\n\t\nfunc _switch_to_goal(new_goal: Goal) -> void:\n\tvar old_intent = current_intent\n\tvar old_goal_name = current_goal.name if current_goal else \"none\"\n\t\n\tcurrent_goal = new_goal\n\ttime_since_goal_change = 0.0\n\t\n\tif new_goal == null:\n\t\tcurrent_intent = Intent.new()\n\t\tcurrent_intent.action = \"idle\"\n\t\tcurrent_intent.goal_name = \"idle\"\n\telse:\n\t\tcurrent_intent = new_goal.generate_intent(self)\n\t\tcurrent_intent.goal_name = new_goal.name\n\t\tcurrent_intent.priority = new_goal.evaluate_priority(self)\n\t\t\n\tgoal_changed.emit(old_goal_name, current_intent.goal_name, current_intent.priority)\n\tintent_changed.emit(old_intent, current_intent)\n\t\nfunc get_current_intent() -> Intent:\n\treturn current_intent\n\t\nfunc force_reevaluate() -> void:\n\tvar best_goal = _evaluate_goals()\n\tvar old_threshold = priority_threshold\n\tpriority_threshold = -INF\n\tif _should_switch_goal(best_goal):\n\t\t_switch_to_goal(best_goal)\n\tpriority_threshold = old_threshold\n\t\nfunc determine_personality() -> void:\n\tpersonality[\"aggression\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"bravery\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"dominance\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"energy\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"nervous\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"sympathy\"] = randf()\n\t\nfunc remember(key: String, value: Variant) -> void:\n\tmemory[key] = value\n\t\nfunc recall(key: String, default = null) -> Variant:\n\treturn memory.get(key, default)\n\t\nfunc forget(key: String) -> void:\n\tmemory.erase(key)\n\t\nfunc has_memory(key: String) -> bool:\n\treturn memory.has(key)\n\t\nfunc clear_memory() -> void:\n\tmemory.clear()\n\t\nfunc get_memory_keys() -> Array:\n\treturn memory.keys()\n\n\n```","x":-12720,"y":-26466,"width":661,"height":2632},
		{"id":"586ed1603f1abc63","type":"file","file":"assets/pico/comit.gif","x":-11181,"y":-17989,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"a64d3fbd06eee781","type":"file","file":"assets/mina/gif_ropejump-2473167005.gif","x":-9795,"y":-18339,"width":481,"height":270},
		{"id":"b559218e16ff74f8","type":"text","text":"# IntentExecutor (ver1)\n```gdscript\nclass_name IntentExecutor\nextends Node\n\n@export var creature: Node2D\nvar current_intent: CreatureIntent\nvar action_handlers: Dictionary = {} # String -> Callable\n\n￼func _ready():\n\t# register built-in handlers\n\t_register_default_handlers()\n\t\n\t# allow components to register their own handlers\n\t_discover_component_handlers() \n\t\n\n\tvar brain = creature.get_node_or_null(\"BrainComponent\")\n\t￼if brain:\n\t\tbrain.intent_changed.connect(_on_intent_changed)\n\t\t\n\t\t\n￼func _register_default_handlers():\n\t# register common action patterns\n\tregister_action(\"idle\", _handle_idle)\n\tregister_action(\"move_to\", _handle_move_to)\n\tregister_action(\"wander\", _handle_wander)\n\tregister_action(\"flee\", _handle_flee)\n\tregister_action(\"follow\", _handle_follow)\n\t\n￼func _discover_component_handlers():\n\t# let components register their own action handlers\n\tfor child in creature.get_children()\n\tif child.has_method(\"register_intent_handlers\"):\n\t\tchild.register_intent_handlers(self)==-\n\t\t\nfunc register_action(action_name: String, handler: Callable):\n\t# public api for components to register handlers\n\taction_handlers[action_name] = handler\t\t\n\t\t\nfunc _on_intent_changed(intent: CreatureIntent):\n\tcurrent_intent = intent\n\t_execute_intent(intent)\n\t\n\t\nfunc _execute_intent(intent: CreatureIntent):\n\tif intent.target_position != Vector2.ZERO or intent.target_entity != null:\n\t\t_handle_movement_to_target(intent)\n\t\t\n\tif intent.look_target != null:\n\t\t_handle_gaze(intent)\n\t\t\n\tif action_handlers.has(intent.action):\n\t\taction_handlers[intent.action].call(intent)\n\telse:\n\t\t_try_component_dispatch(intent)\n\t\t\nfunc _try_component_dispatch(intent: CreatureIntent):\n\t# try to find a component that can handle this action\n\tfor child in creature.get_children():\n\t\tif child.has_method(\"handle_intent\"):\n\t\t\tif child.handle_intent(intent):\n\t\t\t\treturn # component handled it\n\t\n# these default methods should probably not be in the intent executor, they should be in the components themselves, dummy\nfunc _handle_movement_to_target(intent: CreatureIntent):\n\tpass\n\t\nfunc _handle_gaze(intent: CreatureIntent):\n\tpass\n\t\nfunc _handle_idle(intent: CreatureIntent):\n\tpass\n\t\nfunc _handle_move_to(intent: CreatureIntent):\n\tpass\n\t\nfunc _handle_wander(intent: CreatureIntent):\n\tpass\n\t\nfunc _handle_flee(intent: CreatureIntent):\n\tpass\n```","x":-11991,"y":-26440,"width":911,"height":1534,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"db0394d3ec561397","type":"file","file":"assets/pico/zaag_194.gif","x":-11181,"y":-18389,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"17c89ec46c1d8b35","type":"file","file":"assets/mina/gif-bossstinky-1643782697452_mcu8.1080-723182484.gif","x":-10279,"y":-17797,"width":484,"height":272},
		{"id":"a4e6fbb4590defe7","type":"file","file":"assets/mina/gif-trinketwisp-1643782697440_7u88-2920988492.gif","x":-10279,"y":-18069,"width":484,"height":272},
